solution: ```class Solution {
    public int numPairsDivisibleBy60(int[] time) {
        int[] rem = new int[60];
        int count = 0;
        for (int t : time) {
            int r = t % 60;
            int need = (60 - r) % 60;
            count += rem[need];
            rem[r]++;
        }
        return count;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single pass through the array, using a fixed-size frequency array to count remainders mod 60. For each song, the required complementary remainder is computed in constant time and the running total is updated.

